<subSubSection id="17D670EA5A3CDC8A33DD8C4B86479C3B" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="65C44F3EE0D3DBAB159020F4A42CEE49" pageNumber="486">etymology Named in honor of the great naturalist and artist Roger Tory Peterson, whose field-guide style inspired the form of the drawings used in this monograph.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="78F528765095980FC623DA76F9151E96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="390C6BB4BAF0FB773EAB22FC1A94B6FC" pageNumber="486">
diagnosis A very distinctive large member of the 
<taxonomicName id="3A293FBDE4DA90603FE8ECB35FD23F27" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group distinguished by its unique sculpturing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2D080320A93473D28681E0DE7B40FFE" type="description">
<paragraph id="B891A91F526A2C47E5F6D4EDAA7E082A" pageNumber="486">Major: brown; mesopleuron and side of propodeum irregularly rugoreticulate; center and sides of pronotum smooth and shiny or at most with scattered punctures; humerus in dorsal-oblique view raised prominently.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C7C11F9B7827EFA5B4D01AB8001B2BC" pageNumber="486">
Minor: yellow; mesopleuron and side of propodeum irregularly rugoreticulate; center and sides of pronotum smooth and shiny or at most with scattered punctures; humerus in dorsal-oblique view a pointed, &quot;sharkfin&quot; shape; occiput narrow surmounted by a thin collar. Similar in body form to 
<taxonomicName id="804C18F4759DDC32D3061B074342B107" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181870" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole erratilis Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole erratilis Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erratilis">erratilis</taxonomicName>
of Costa Rica, which species lacks the rugoreticulum, has longer pilosity, and more extensive cephalic carinulae. See also the less similar 
<taxonomicName id="BD661FCD3EEE6BED58D7EBFC7CB2788D" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181839" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulifera">angulifera</taxonomicName>
, ecuadorana, 
<taxonomicName id="F68B7AE9C4EC43B3120BBC783BE0B617" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182066" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole polita Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole polita Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">polita</taxonomicName>
(in the 
<taxonomicName id="ED5DB3DE5D286E9DEE4855F409B2E6F7" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group), 
<taxonomicName id="749FC064CB2B4C05498CA4F41C26F960" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181939" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmalzi">schmalzi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F83C0EA3785235D9587DF86D349004F2" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181946" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole styrax Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole styrax Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styrax">styrax</taxonomicName>
. measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.08, HL 1.14, SL 0.64, EL 0.18, PW 0.58. Paratype minor: HW 0.60, HL 0.66, SL 0.66, EL 0.14, PW 0.40.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541387E8A2B79F8D77EF2008D1616C5B" pageNumber="486">Color Major: medium to dark and slightly reddish brown, tarsi light yellowish brown. Minor: medium brown, tarsi brownish yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3280EAC04C111EBBB8BCEA519C72F928" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6BB61D74F1A80E5A40D0C3C13ED0C2B3" pageNumber="486">range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1ED259E9563DBDA85A8977B6030BF138" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="7DB453E6E7045BA94B505449EF10AE0C" pageNumber="486">Biology New second-growth forest, on bananas and Piper; a colony was found nesting in a dead Piper stem (Longino 1997).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
